{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "02", "m": "06", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "02", "M": "31", "S": "53"}}, "news": [{"title": "Dalmandi drive gains pace, 112 buildings demolished so far in Varanasi", "para": "Demolition for the Dalmandi road-widening project has resumed, with over 112 structures razed to improve access to Kashi Vishwanath Dham. The project, aiming to widen the 650-meter road to 17.4 meters, has seen over 90 buildings acquired and compensation exceeding \u20b950 crore disbursed. Negotiations continue for six mosques in the project's path.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/infrastructure/dalmandi-drive-gains-pace-112-buildings-demolished-so-far-in-varanasi/131437452?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-1565799/131437452.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "infrastructure"}, {"title": "Why India\u2019s $105 billion GCC opportunity is a turning point for real estate", "para": "India's Global Capability Centres are transforming into innovation hubs, driving significant growth in the real estate sector.  Projected to reach $100-110 billion by 2030, these centres are demanding new cities, formats, and higher quality commercial and residential spaces, reshaping India's urban landscape.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/blog/indias-growing-gcc-market-a-105-billion-transformation-for-real-estate/131437651?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-110732/131437651.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "indias-growing-gcc-market-a-105-billion-transformation-for-real-estate"}, {"title": "Odisha housing board set to expand affordable housing with four projects", "para": "Odisha State Housing Board plans four major projects for FY 2026-27, aiming to deliver nearly 6,877 inclusive residential units. These include the Suango PPP project, Ranasinghpur EPC housing, Patrapada housing, and Basanti Colony joint venture. The board is also seeking government land for affordable housing initiatives to address urban housing needs.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/odisha-housing-board-set-to-expand-affordable-housing-with-four-projects/131437400?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-47124/131437400.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}